# Inter typography (StartupMatch)

Use the project’s downloadable Inter font families from `app/src/main/res/font/`. Do **not** rely on `textStyle="bold"` alone for brand typography — set `fontFamily` to the correct Inter weight.

## Mapping

| Role | Font resource | When to use |
|------|----------------|-------------|
| **Title (bold)** | `@font/inter_bold` | Screen/section titles, primary headings, hero titles |
| **Title description / subtitle** | `@font/inter_light` | Secondary lines under a title, taglines, intro blurbs |
| **Standard body** | `@font/inter_medium` | Paragraphs, labels (if not title), list body, hints when neutral |
| **Button or link** | `@font/inter_semibold` | `MaterialButton`, text links (`TextView` acting as link), emphasized inline actions |

## Android XML

- Prefer: `android:fontFamily="@font/<name>"` on `TextView` / `Button`.
- Material: `app:fontFamily="@font/<name>"` when the view supports it.
- Keep `textSize`/`lineSpacing` from design; this rule only fixes **family/weight**.

## Examples (conceptual)

- Main screen title → `inter_bold`
- Line under the title (“Welcome” subtitle) → `inter_light`
- Form field label or long description → `inter_medium` (unless it is a link → `inter_semibold`)
- “Continue”, “Login”, “Sign up” → `inter_semibold`

## Consistency

When adding or editing layouts (`*.xml`) or styles, apply this mapping so onboarding, auth, and future screens stay visually consistent.
